      <text>HELM 32.2 E4 Consistency</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**32.2 E4 Consistency**

The  following linear multistep scheme is given: 

{@lside=h*rside@}

Determine the first four coefficients \\\(c_k\\\) of the truncation error expression

\\\(\tau_{j}=\frac{1}{\beta h}\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}c_{k}h^{k}y^{(k)}(jh)\\\)

\\\(c_0,\, c_1,\, c_2,\, c_3=\\\) [[input:S_cp]] [[validation:S_cp]] [[feedback:cp]] 

Hence, what is the order of the scheme?

[[input:S_o]] [[validation:S_o]] [[feedback:o]] 


Specify the first characteristic polynomial:

\\\(\rho(z)=\\\) [[input:S_rho]] [[validation:S_rho]] [[feedback:rho]] 



Determine the roots of this polynomial. Provide a list with square brackets like <code>[1, 2]</code>. The order of the values is not important. Multiple roots must be repeated, e.g. \\\(\[1,1\]\\\)

\\\(\{z_1,z_2\}=\\\) [[input:S_sol]] [[validation:S_sol]] [[feedback:sol]]

The scheme is therefore [[input:S_ZS]]. [[validation:S_ZS]] [[feedback:ZS]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
